This article is a transcript of remarks made at the funeral service for Richard G. Lugar, a former mayor of Indianapolis and senator from Indiana. The remarks were delivered by Vice President Mike Pence, who praised Lugar's life of service and his many accomplishments. Pence highlighted Lugar's role in transforming Indianapolis into a dynamic capital city and his contributions to foreign affairs, particularly in nuclear disarmament. He also emphasized Lugar's reputation as a respected statesman and his ability to inspire and mentor future leaders. Pence concluded by celebrating Lugar's devotion to his family and his faith, and expressed condolences to Lugar's loved ones.